profile_positions.description:
Signify, formerly known as Philips Lighting, is the world leader in lighting solutions.

•	Support the execution of TIAs & PIAs on Signify initiatives in which personal data are processed, including 
        mitigation plans, follow-up actions and risk reporting;
     •	Support the Signify Privacy team in handling privacy requests, speed-up initiatives and campaigns, develop, 
        maintain and manage Privacy Awareness and Communication Program, drafting notifications facilitating 
        compliance with Global Privacy Laws that affect business directly or otherwise;
    •	Collaborate with Signify Privacy team on wide projects such as:
                       o	set-up of the Privacy Office;
                       o	take part in the definition and review of policies and procedures;
                       o	conduct analysis work of new regulatory changes communicated by Standards & Regulations 
                                (S&L) Group; and
                      o	drafting data breach form and privacy policies applicable in specific countries where Signify 
                                conducts business.
     •	Facilitate the compliance throughout Signify wrt the processing of the relevant personal data / organizations;
     •	Connect with the relevant organizations and manage the privacy impacts on the relevant initiatives;
     •	Spread awareness within the company wrt Personal Data;
      •	Support the implementation of the privacy compliance framework as required by the Chief Privacy Officer
     •	Provide legal support to Procurement organization on privacy related matters for Procurement;
     •	Act as a focal point for any privacy related issues;
     •	Conduct presentations in meetings (i.e. Quarterly Global Privacy Team Meeting, Monthly Legal Compliance and 
        Internal Privacy Meetings);
     •	Act as first level of support within Signify;
